 normally welcomed the cover the rain provided, today in West Commons the rain was cut with a cold wind from the North.<br>
<br>
&quot;I am getting too old for this&quot; thought Mayl.  <br>
<br>
While only 100 years of age, as a son of a human bar wench and an elven Ranger, Mayl was feeling his human side more and more of late.  Raised in the slums of Freeport after his elven &quot;father&quot; return to the call of the woods, he had lead a rough life.  Only his quick hands and faster feet had kept him alive this long.  Learning the ways of a rogue came naturally to Mayl.  <br>
<br>
Due to recent &quot;misunderstanding&quot; between his guild leader and himself, Mayl thought that it would be a good time to be away from Freeport.  Or at least to return to Freeport when he was enough coin to sooth some hurt feelings.<br>
<br>
With that in mind Mayl made his first trip to Befallen to work on some skills that had grown rusty of late.<br>
<br>
The entrance was easy enough to find with it's unearthly light glowing in the distance.<br>
<br>
A quick duck in the shadows and soon Mayl was inside Befallen.  <br>
<br>
&quot;I wonder why all those folks are standing by that door&quot; thought Mayl.<br>
<br>
The high elf mage pulled and pulled at the door while a hulking troll swung his axe into the wood.<br>
<br>
&quot;silly fools&quot; said Mayl.<br>
<br>
&quot;U cod doo beter&quot; spit the troll.<br>
<br>
&quot;step aside slim&quot; muttered Mayl<br>
<br>
with a quick flick of a tool, the door sprung open. <br>
<br>
With a suprised look the troll and mage ran thru the doorway.<br>
<br>
Being an intelligent robe, the high elf invited Mayl to hunt the lower levels with his troll partner.<br>
<br>
&quot;ah a meat shield and robe&quot; thought Mayl.  <br>
<br>
As they approached the broken stairway down below, a cold breeze with the smell of decay blew by them.<br>
<br>
&quot;hmm something smells good&quot; said the troll.<br>
<br>
Mayl began to wonder what he is getting himself into.<br>
